@NODE ENG_INTRO "Introduction"
Win-2-Front is a simple commodity which has ability to bring windows to front.
Forget about managing windows using depth gadget.
@ENDNODE
@NODE ENG_DISTR "Distribution"
Win-2-Front may be freely distributed as long as nothing is changed and no
charge is made. If you'll modify (improve) source code then send me a copy
with comments.
@ENDNODE
@NODE ENG_DISCL "Disclaimer"
I accept no responsibility for any loss/damage caused by using this proggy.
@ENDNODE
@NODE ENG_DESCR "Description"
Sometimes I have to work on PC under Windows (brrrr) and I found there a very
handy method of window switching using LAlt-TAB combination. I couldn't find
Amiga-based tool with this ability so I wrote this program.

It uses the same keyboard combination as PC uses (left alt-tab) and displays
small window with title of the window, which should be popped to front. If a
window has no title program displays "Unnamed". Selected window will be moved
in front of all other windows and activated right after releasing LEFT-ALT key.

Font used for rendering window name could be selected by arguments/tooltypes:
FONTNAME and FONTSIZE (i.e. FONTNAME=Times.font FONTSIZE=24). If one of these
parameters is not specified or desired font could not be opened, program uses
screen font.
@ENDNODE
@NODE ENG_FEAT "Features"
- It's a commodity (put it in your WBStartup drawer),
- Ignores backdrop windows and of course own window,
- Blocks mouse so no window could be closed (Amiga has so good multitasking
  that I have to do this),
- Works only on default public screen (Workbench in most cases),
- User-defined program priority by standard commodity methods,
- User-defined font,
- Starting program when another copy is working removes both copies (the same
  as selecting 'Remove' in Exchange program).
- Fully system compliant
@ENDNODE
@NODE ENG_REQ "Requirements"
- Any Amiga computer with KickStart 2.0+.
@ENDNODE
@NODE ENG_FUTURE "Future"
I have some ideas but I'm too lazy to introduce them, but if you mail me with
your suggestions or bug report then I try to develop this proggy :-)

My suggestions:
- Support for screens other than default public,
- Shorter code (own startup module),
- User-defined key combination,
- Better filtering function.
@ENDNODE
@NODE ENG_BUGS "Bugs"
I'm using this program on my A1200 with:
 - BlizzardPPC 603e/266 and 040/30
 - 2 MB Chip RAM + 32 MB Fast RAM,
 - Kickstart 3.1 (40.68),
 - Workbench 3.1 (40.29),
and it works excellent.
@ENDNODE
@NODE ENG_ME "Contact"
Mail me at: jrzeuski@neptun.gdansk.tpsa.pl
@ENDNODE

